CoinDescription: It is a standard circulation coin for 1 Paisa denomination. It was minted during the period of (1965-1981). It is made up of Aluminium. It weights 0.75g with 17mm diameter and 1.72mm thickness. On heads, it features Ashoka Stambh at centre with 'India' written around it in English and Hindi. On tails side we see denomination written at centre with 'Paise' written around it in English and Hindi. It also have date of minting below the denomination.
